post_text: A very special thank you to Miss Newcomer and the Durand FFA students that provided backpacks and supplies for a few of our students! Our families really appreciated your generosity. ‚ù§Ô∏è
shared_text:
Durand FFA
August 31 at 5:51 PM ¬∑

On Monday, August 31, 2020 the Durand FFA presented the Durand Elementary School with 5 backpacks full of supplies as part of the Illinois Foundation FFA's Day of Service Project. As part of the 92nd Annual Illinois FFA Convention, the Durand FFA purchased school supplies for 5 Durand Elementary students. The Illinois FFA Has Your Back Project tasked every FFA in the state to provide supplies for students in their districts.

Pictured are the 5 Durand FFA Officers shopping for supplies. Left to right: Josh Erickson (Secretary), Amber Lee (Treasurer), Anna Johnson (Vice President), Tyler Lee (President, and Rachel Proctor (Reporter).

Also pictured is Reporter, Rachel Proctor, presenting Durand Elementary Principal, Mrs. Rufener, with one of the backpacks.

post_text: Preschool screening will be held on August 31st from 8-12 and 1-3 by appointment only. This screening will be done virtually through Google Meet. A link will be emailed to you on August 28th. The structure for the 2020/2021 school year is that students receiving special services will be invited to attend in person learning each day from 8-10:45AM. Students that do not demonstrate a need for specialized services, but do meet our eligibility criteria will be invited to participate virtually during our afternoon sessions. If you have any questions, please email Mrs. Leskowich. Please call the Elementary Office to set up an appointment at 815-248-2171. Screenings are available for students who will be three on or before September 1st. If you have developmental concerns about your child and they are under the age of three, feel free to contact Mrs. Leskowich at bleskowich@cusd322.org for further guidance regarding your child‚Äôs development. Thank you!

post_text:
Hello Elementary Families,

I hope this finds you well and enjoying your summer. As you are aware, we are currently having many discussions about what back to school may look like. There are many factors for the team to discuss and consider as we develop those plans. We will be surveying families again in the near future to get more input as well. One thing we do know for certain is that WE WILL NOT BE OFFERING BEFORE OR AFTER SCHOOL CARE as the 2020-2021 school year begins. It is possible that those services will resume when restrictions are lifted, but as of now, we must focus on the safety of our students and staff during school hours only. We understand that this will inconvenience several of our families; therefore, we wanted to let you know as soon as possible so that you have time to make other arrangements for before and after school care. Please contact myself or Mr. Alberstett if you have additional questions regarding our decision to cancel before and after school care given the current pandemic. Thank you and stay well.

Shanna Rufener
Elementary Principal

One thing we do know for certain is that WE WILL NOT BE OFFERING BEFORE OR AFTER SCHOOL CARE as the 2020-2021 school year begins. It is possible that those services will resume when restrictions are lifted, but as of now, we must focus on the safety of our students and staff during school hours only. We understand that this will inconvenience several of our families; therefore, we wanted to let you know as soon as possible so that you have time to make other arrangements for before and after school care. Please contact myself or Mr. Alberstett if you have additional questions regarding our decision to cancel before and after school care given the current pandemic. Thank you and stay well.

Shanna Rufener
Elementary Principal

post_text:
Hello Durand Families,

On Friday, April 10, 2020, the lights at the football field will be on from 7:30-9:30 p.m. to show support for our Durand students, staff and community. We are going to participate in the "Be the Light" campaign. It brings light to those fighting COVID-19 and honors all students who have lost school experiences. We want everyone to know how much we support our essential workers and their dedication and unwavering perseverance.

We understand the tremendous anxiety and emotional toll this has been on many of you. Please take some time and drive by the field if you get an opportunity. Please be cautious and supportive of social distance with no gatherings.

We wish everyone a safe and happy Easter.
text:
Hello Durand Families,

On Friday, April 10, 2020, the lights at the football field will be on from 7:30-9:30 p.m. to show support for our Durand students, staff and community. We are going to participate in the "Be the Light" campaign. It brings light to those fighting COVID-19 and honors all students who have lost school experiences. We want everyone to know how much we support our essential workers and their dedication and unwavering perseverance.

We understand the tremendous anxiety and emotional toll this has been on many of you. Please take some time and drive by the field if you get an opportunity. Please be cautious and supportive of social distance with no gatherings.

We wish everyone a safe and happy Easter.

post_text: Because the Durand 5K will be cancelled this year, we have decided to send the same message and use the shirt design, but change the words Durand 5K to Quarantine 2020. Anyone can order a shirt by mailing the order form (or a piece of paper with your sizes on it) to the school. The theme for this year was going to be BE THE LIGHT IN SOMEONE ELSE'S DARKNESS. We feel that this message is better than ever right now considering we are practicing social isolation and really recognizing the power of human connection. There is no better time to be the positive light for others whether it be via a vehicle parade, a picture message, a handwritten note or a video chat. Help us send this message by purchasing and wearing one of our shirts! Orders due by next Friday, 4/17.

Hello Families! We hope that you are all safe and healthy at home. We continue to work on our end to create balance for our families at home. We are also using the results from the survey that you completed to make changes for Remote Learning as needed. This article may describe similar obstacles that some of our families may be facing so we wanted to share it. Please know that you are not alone. We are working diligently to stay connected with our families and to keep our students engaged, but we also need you to know that your health, safety and well being are the top priority. Family comes first, so do what you can. We appreciate you all so much during this very difficult time! Have a great weekend üíô

post_text:
Durand Schools will be closed Monday, March 16. No e-Learning will be assigned for tomorrow and no staff will be in the building. It is our duty to inform you that a Durand staff member who works at the Dolan Education Center has been placed on quarantine for possible exposure to someone who tested positive for the Coronavirus. This person has been asked to self-quarantine as a precautionary measure and they have exhibited no symptoms of the virus. The Durand Administration will meet tomorrow to conduct further planning. We will put out another message before Tuesday regarding e-Learning, but again, nothing is expected to be done tomorrow. Please note that the earliest Durand Schools will be back in session will be Tuesday, March 31. All activities are cancelled until at least the March 31 date. Thank you for your patience during this difficult time.

Sincerely,
Kurt Alberstett

Please note that the earliest Durand Schools will be back in session will be Tuesday, March 31. All activities are cancelled until at least the March 31 date. Thank you for your patience during this difficult time.

Sincerely,
Kurt Alberstett

post_text:
Dear Families,

Due to the Coronavirus pandemic, Governor Pritzker has ordered that all schools in Illinois close from Tuesday, March 17 through Monday, March 30. Durand Schools will be utilizing eLearning strategies beginning on Tuesday, March 17, 2020. In order to make sure that all of our students and families are as prepared as possible to continue with learning via eLearning, we will be releasing our students at 11:30AM on Monday, March 16, 2020. This will allow our administrative team and staff to prepare communications to parents explaining the expectations and procedures of eLearning as well as the electronic platforms in which the students will access their learning materials/activities.

The health and safety of our students and staff is our top priority. It is important to note that there are no confirmed cases of Coronavirus within our schools or Winnebago County at this time. Instead, this is a precautionary measure intended to minimize the possibility of community spread.

Thank you,
Kurt Alberstett
Superintendent

Sign your kids up for some fun & help the Pecatonica Rotary at the same time!!! Rotary sends four Pecatoncia HS students to a three day leadership camp each spring & also awards four $1,000 scholarships to local HS seniors. Rotary does great things for the youth in our community and money raised from this event will help them continue their efforts. So get out & support the Rotary with their fundraiser üèÄ
